{{Refimprove|date=July 2012}} {{Infobox video game |title = The Political Machine 2012 |image = |developer = [[Stardock]] |publisher = |designer = |engine = |released = July 31, 2012 |genre = [[Government simulation game|Government simulation]] |modes = [[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]] }}
'''''The Political Machine 2012''''' is a [[government simulation game]] from [[Stardock]] and the third game in ''[[The Political Machine (series)|The Political Machine]]'' series, in which the player leads a [[election campaign|campaign]] to elect the [[President of the United States]]. The player accomplishes this goal by traveling from state to state and engaging in a variety of activities to either raise money or raise [[Opinion poll|poll]] numbers.
==Reception== {{Video game reviews | MC = 54/100<ref name=MC>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/the-political-machine-2012 |title=The Political Machine 2012 for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=May 9, 2016}}</ref> | GSpot = 6/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Todd |first=Brett |date=August 3, 2012 |url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/the-political-machine-2012-review/1900-6390200/ |title=The Political Machine 2012 Review |publisher=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> | IGN = 6.5/10<ref>{{cite web |last=Johnson |first=Leif |date=August 9, 2012 |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/08/09/the-political-machine-2012-review |title=The Political Machine 2012 Review |publisher=[[IGN]] |accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> }}
The game received "mixed" reviews according to video game [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]].<ref name=MC/>
